In [36]:
for i in num.columns:
    #print(df[i])
    q1 = num[i].quantile(0.25)
    q3 = num[i].quantile(0.75)
    
    IQR = q3-q1
    lower = q1 - (1.5*IQR)
    upper = q3 + (1.5*IQR)
    num[(num[i]<lower)] = lower
    num[(num[i]>upper)] = upper
    print(f"{i} Lower {lower} ")
    print(f"{i} Upper {upper}")
    print()
